{{setTitle     "YUI CSS"}}
{{setSubTitle  "A set of small, responsive CSS modules that you can use in every web project."}}
{{setActiveNav "home"}}

{{addLocalCSS "/css/home.css"}}

<div class="hero">
    <h1 class="yui3-u-1">{{title}}</h1>
    <h2 class="yui3-u-3-4 l-centered">{{subTitle}}</h2>
</div>


<div class="yui3-g-r">
    <div class="yui3-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Your CSS foundation.</h3>
            <p>
                YUI CSS builds on normalize.css and provides layout and styling for native HTML elements, plus the most common UI components. It's what you need, without the cruft.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="yui3-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Made with mobile in mind.</h3>
            <p>
                YUI CSS is responsive out-of-the-box, so elements look great on all screen sizes. Customize your styles with the SkinBuilder to make your style your own.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="yui3-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Stays out of your way.</h3>
            <p>
                YUI CSS has minimal styles and encourages you to write your application styles on top of it. It's designed to get out of your way and makes it easy to override styles.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="yui3-g-r">
    <div class="yui3-u-1">
        <h3 class="l-hbox">CSS with the tiniest footprint.</h3>

        <div class="size-chart l-vbox yui3-g">
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-base yui3-u" style="width: 25%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.base}}">
                    Base <span class="size-chart-size">(1.2KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-grids yui3-u" style="width: 14.5%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.grids}}">
                    Grids <span class="size-chart-size">(0.7KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-forms yui3-u"style="width: 27%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.forms}}">
                    Forms <span class="size-chart-size">(1.3KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-tables yui3-u" style="width: 12.5%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.tables}}">
                    Tables <span class="size-chart-size">(0.6KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-lists yui3-u" style="width: 21%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.lists}}">
                    Navigation <span class="size-chart-size">(1KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="l-hbox">
            YUI CSS is ridiculously tiny. The entire set of modules clocks in at <strong>4.8KB minified and gzipped</strong>, without forgoing responsive styles, design, or ease of use. Crafted with mobile devices in mind, it was important to us to keep our file sizes small and every line of CSS was carefully considered. If you decide to only use a subset of these modules, you'll save even more bytes.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
